A fly on the has gathered information that Royal AM are looking to put their money where their mouth is in the coming season. This means that the club wants to become a powerhouse in South African football, and they are ready to flex their financial muscle to lure the best stars to their club. READ ALSO: AmaZulu confident despite ‘tough’ Champions League draw “The club has the resources, there is no doubt about that. The bosslady, Shawn Mkhize, wants to transform Royal AM into something like Manchester City of England,” said a source. The spy continued: “Look at Mamelodi Sundowns, they were living in the shadow of Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates until Patrice Motsepe brought the riches, now the tables have turned. MaMkhize wants to do the same.”